{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require all public places to have toilets accessible with a medical card",
        "additional_details": "I have a medical condition myself which affects my bowel and makes it very hard to know when you need to go to the toilet, it is very embarrassing 1 minute of fine the next you need to go. I am fed up with getting refused access to toilets at garages etc because people may not know what a medical card is. If it's law that they have to let people with a medical card go to the toilet then I think it would create a better community and also a better understanding that people have underlying disabilities.",
        "background": "Require all places that serve the community i.e garages, shops give access to customers to use a toilet and anyone with a medical card, such as a \u2018Just can\u2019t wait\u2019 card, can use any toilet they need.",
